Week End Thoughts&hellip;
I decided to move my Thoughtful Thursday since I am participating in We Are THAT Family&rsquo;s Sincerely Fro' Me to You carnival on Thursdays. Since &ldquo;Thoughtful Thursday&rdquo; is something I made up, it seems trivial to move the day&hellip; same theme, only we&rsquo;ll call it Week End Thoughts&hellip;
Week End Thoughts:
My posts typically relate funny anecdotes about the happenings of a stay at home wife and mom with three kids.

Last week as we were running errands the Christian radio station played one of those 60 sec minisermons. The person was speaking on 1 John 4 and read the passage which states, &ldquo;This is love: not that we loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son as an atoning sacrifice for our sins.&rdquo;
Son: &quot; Mom, why did she say we don&rsquo;t love God?&quot;
Me: &ldquo;They were saying that we didn&rsquo;t love God first, but that God loved us and then we loved him.

Yesterday when we were out running errands my son told me,
&ldquo;Mom, I am going to be really good at nap time today.&rdquo;
I was in the midst of trying to find the things on my mental list and push the cart with three kids on it, so I muttered something like, &ldquo;good honey&rdquo; and continued on. My son was so excited because after nap time we were going to plant flowers in our yard.

This afternoon my son asked if he could, &ldquo;have some Charlie Brown candy&rdquo;. It took me a few minutes to figure out what he meant.
&ldquo;Peanuts?&rdquo; I asked.
&ldquo;No&rdquo;
Then I realized, &ldquo;Oh Peppermint Patty?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yup!&rdquo;
I think I may start calling them that from now on :-)

This morning when my kids were eating breakfast my son asked,
&ldquo;Mom, what happened to your flower?&rdquo; I looked on the deck and it was gone. I asked my hubby if he moved it and he said,&quot; No, but last night when I was sitting out at the dining room table, I did hear a  crash outside when the wind blew.&quot;
My kids went out to investigate this morning and it seems my poor flower decided to take her life with a fateful jump off of our deck, rather than to continue to suffer under my care.
